+# 0230 - EventBus Passive Supervisor Sink
+
+Patch 0230 resumes functional work after the 0227 gate and the 0229 triage.
+The triage allows functional resumption because runtime review is clear.
+
+The implemented cable is deliberately minimal and direct:
+
+```text
+Scheduler / RouteProxy / ControlProxy / SHM / Policy / GitHub / SQL / Qdrant / Rehydrate / Pushback
+  -> existing EventBus contract / canonical EventBus event
+  -> PassiveSupervisorSink.accept(event)
+  -> CellularState via existing build_cellular_snapshot
+  -> optional snapshot
+  -> optional audit/replay
+```
+
+## What is reused
+
+The patch updates `src/context/passive_bus_supervisor_cellular_snapshot.py` instead
+of creating a parallel runtime. It reuses:
+
+- `BusSupervisorEvent`
+- `event_from_mapping`
+- `build_cellular_snapshot`
+- `PassiveBusSupervisorSnapshot`
+- the 0220 passive authority boundary
+
+## Scheduler boundary
+
+Scheduler remains the upstream orchestration authority. It may emit or expose
+canonical EventBus events, but the passive supervisor must not call
+`Scheduler.run`, dispatch handlers, or make scheduling decisions.
+
+## EventBus boundary
+
+Patch 0230 does not implement a new EventBus. It accepts canonical event mappings
+that represent events already transported by the EventBus. The smoke tool uses
+JSON/JSONL only as a test/replay harness.
+
+## Optional outputs
+
+`snapshot.json` and `events.jsonl` are optional outputs. They are not the normal
+runtime path. The normal path is:
+
+```text
+EventBus -> PassiveSupervisorSink -> CellularState
+```
+
+The snapshot and audit are optional outputs for human inspection, tests, replay,
+and future VisPy views.
+
+## Authority boundary
+
+The supervisor remains downstream-only and must not:
+
+- run Scheduler
+- control RouteProxy or ControlProxy
+- mutate SHM
+- decide policy
+- call GitHub APIs
+- write SQL
+- write Qdrant
+- execute rehydration
+- push back status or results
