+# 0230 EventBus Passive Supervisor Sink Rule
+
+Patch 0230 may resume functional supervision only because 0229 triage reports no
+runtime review requirement.
+
+Required behavior:
+
+- Update the existing passive bus supervisor surface.
+- Reuse `BusSupervisorEvent`, `event_from_mapping`, and `build_cellular_snapshot`.
+- Accept canonical EventBus events downstream-only.
+- Keep Scheduler as upstream orchestration authority.
+- Keep snapshot and audit/replay optional.
+
+Forbidden behavior:
+
+- must not introduce a new EventBus
+- must not call `Scheduler.run`
+- must not dispatch scheduler handlers
+- must not control RouteProxy or ControlProxy
+- must not claim or release proxy leases
+- must not mutate SHM or mmap buffers
+- must not decide policy
+- must not call GitHub APIs
+- must not write SQL
+- must not write or query Qdrant
+- must not execute rehydration
+- must not push back GitHub/project status
+- must not add non-stdlib dependencies
+
+The live runtime path remains:
+
+```text
+EventBus -> PassiveSupervisorSink -> CellularState
+```
+
+Any file-based JSON or JSONL input in tools is a smoke/replay harness only.
